               <head>Four works on sufism</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010113603">
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 576a" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_576-item1">
                     <locus from="3r" to="28r">ff. 3r-28r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23273">Aẕkār al-aḥrār </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23273">اذکار الاحیار</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">و ذكر مجلس و مکارم اولاد عالی نزاد و ذکر خیر بعضی
                                مستفیدان پاک نهاد علی الاجمال با ان ضمیمه ساخته شود</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">ا انصرنا یا خیر الناصرین و ارقنا شفاعة سید
                                المرسلین و حمایة اله ا اصحبه الی یوم الدین قد تم التحریر نسخه
                                المسماة بازکار الاحرار نصف من رجب المرجب سنه ۲۲ جلوس محمد شاه پادشاه
                                غازی </explicit>
                     <colophon>Completed in the middle of Rajab 11th year of Muḥammad S̲h̲āh
                                (AH 1141, Feb 1729). </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>An account of the saint <persName role="tch" key="person_f8377">Mīr Abū
                                        ’l-ʿUlā Naqshbandī Akbarābādī</persName> - whose full name
                                    is given on f. 5v as Amīr Abū ’l-ʿUlā ibn Amīr Abī ‘l-Vafāʾ ibn
                                    Amīr ʿAbd al-Salām, who was born in 990/1582 at Nārēlah near
                                    Delhi and who died on 9 Ṣafar 1061/1651 and was buried at
                                    Akbarābād (i.e. Āgrah). Completed in 1682 by an unnamed disciple
                                    and arranged in seven chapters (<term>bāb</term>) and a
                                    conclusion (<term>khātimah</term>). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning with only the final six and a half
                                    lines of the preface preserved. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian
                                        Manuscripts in the India Office Library, vol. III</title>,
                                        <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!9_f200r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/9, ff. 200-203. </ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>C.A. Storey, <title>Persian Literature: A Bio-bibliographical
                                    Survey</title>, in <title>Storey Online</title>
                           <biblScope>
                              <ref target="https://referenceworks.brillonline.com/entries/storey-online/1322-biography-saints-mystics-etc-saints-mystics-etc-2-COM_10213022#V1-1338" type="n/a">, vol.6 §1338. </ref>
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 576b" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_576-item2">
                     <locus from="28v" to="30v">ff. 28v-30v</locus>
                     <author key="person_65292796">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā, 1338 or
                                    9-1420 </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">خواجه محمد پارسا‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23274">Taḥqīqāt-i Muḥammad Pārsā </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23274">تحیقات محمد پارسا</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">از تحقیقات خواجه محمد پارسا قدس الله سره الاصفیا
                                قال حجة الاسلام حق سبحانه و تعلی در دل آدمی سر نهاده است
                                الخ</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">لوازم معانی را چگونه باید کرد</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>On ecstasy and music (<term>vajd</term> and <term>samāʻ</term>)
                                    and other basic mystical doctrines, most likely compiled from a
                                    work by the Naqshbandi Shaykh <persName role="aut" key="viaf_65292796">Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā</persName>, 1338
                                    or 9-1420.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f033r" type="n/a">Mss Eur 207/13, f. 33. </ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 576c" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_576-itemc">
                     <locus from="39v" to="40r">ff. 30v-40r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f8379">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Abū al-Qāsim ibn Muḥammad ibn
                                    Masʻūd</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">ابو القاسم بن محمد بن مسعود‏ </persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">الحمد لولیله و الصلاة و السلام علی نبیه حضرت حامل
                                عرش الشرح … حضرت خواجه پارساالخ</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">و این دلیل کمال حال و حقیقت ایشانست والله اعلم
                                بالصواب</explicit>
                     <colophon>Colophon dated 22 Rajab of the 11th year of Muhammad Shāh (21
                                Feb 1729). </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>A selection without title of notes and queries on Sufism by Abū
                                    al-Qāsim ibn Muḥammad ibn Masʻūd from the writings of ‘Khvājah
                                    Pārsā’, most likely the Naqshbandi Shaykh <persName role="aut" key="viaf_65292796">Khvājah Muḥammad Pārsā</persName>. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f034r" type="n/a">Mss Eur 207/13, f. 34. </ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 576d" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_576-itemd">
                     <locus from="40r" to="42r">ff. 40r-42r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23275">Risālah-ʼi ṭarīqah-ʼi ḥaz̤arāt-i
                                khvājagān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23275">رسالهٔ طریقهٔ حضرات خواجگان</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">سر رشته دولت ای برادر بکف آر و این عمر گرامی
                                بحسارت مگذار الخ</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">جمله سر؟ خاص و علم گفته شد واسلام و
                                الکرام</explicit>
                     <colophon>Undated but gives the name of the title. </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rules and guidance for members of the Naqshbandi branch of
                                    Sufism, compiled by an unnamed author. </p>
                        <p>Continued (ff. 42r-42v) by an unidentified text in the same hand. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
                                        the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!13_f035r" type="n/a">Mss Eur 207/13, f. 35. </ref>. 
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
